    "description": "Cardiac sarcoidosis is a rare inflammatory disease characterized by the formation of granulomas, or small clusters of inflammatory cells, in the heart tissue. This condition is a manifestation of systemic sarcoidosis, which primarily affects the lungs but can involve multiple organs, including the heart. The presence of these granulomas can disrupt normal heart function, leading to various cardiac complications such as arrhythmias, heart block, and heart failure, making early diagnosis and management essential.",
    "symptoms": [
